# Purpose: Generate new page scaffolds following OpenSchool patterns.

You are building a new page for OpenSchool. Follow these rules exactly:

## Template Structure

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="light">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{PAGE_TITLE}} – OpenSchool</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>

    <header class="app-header">
        <div class="brand">
            <img src="assets/logo-placeholder.svg" alt="OpenSchool" width="32" height="32">
            <span>OpenSchool</span>
        </div>
        <div class="header-actions">
            <button id="theme-toggle" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm" aria-label="Toggle theme">
                <span class="theme-toggle__label">Dark</span>
            </button>
            <button id="logout-btn">Logout</button>
        </div>
    </header>

    <nav class="sidebar" id="sidebar" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <!-- Use same nav items as index.html -->
    </nav>

    <main id="main-content" class="main-content">
        <h1>{{PAGE_TITLE}}</h1>
        <!-- Page content here -->
    </main>

    <div id="toast-container" class="toast-container" aria-live="polite"></div>
    <div id="modal-overlay" class="modal-overlay" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true">
            <div class="modal-header"><h2 id="modal-title"></h2><button class="modal-close" aria-label="Close">&times;</button></div>
            <div class="modal-body" id="modal-body"></div>
            <div class="modal-footer" id="modal-footer"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script type="module" src="js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Rules

1. Always include skip-link, ARIA landmarks, and lang attribute.
2. Use semantic elements (`<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<article>`).
3. Every interactive element needs `aria-label` or visible label.
4. Use CSS classes from existing components — avoid inline styles.
5. For pages in `pages/` subdirectory, prefix paths with `../`.
6. Include toast and modal containers for JS module compatibility.
7. Use `data-role` attributes if content varies by user role.
